Task: Finalize the Corefinity Control Panel into a fully interactive, production-ready SaaS application.
​1. Interactive Environments (All Tabs):
​Pods & Nodes: Create a "Live Monitoring" effect. Use a timer to make the CPU and RAM usage percentages fluctuate slightly (e.g., 42% -> 44%). This makes the dashboard feel connected to real servers.
​Firewall (Functional): Enable the "Add IP" button. When clicked, the new IP should appear in the table immediately. Add a "Delete" icon to remove entries.
​Autoscaler & Monitors: Populate these with mock toggle switches and sliders that users can adjust.
​2. Advanced Deployment Logic (The Prize Winner):
​Pipeline Logic: Use React state to strictly enforce the dropdown sequence (Pipeline -> Provider -> Repository -> Branch).
​Live Progress: In the "Deployment Tasks" tab, add a progress bar to the top-most task. When the page loads, make it animate from 0% to 100% with status text updating (e.g., "Cloning Repo," "Running Build," "Clean up").
​Rollback Feature: Make the "Rollback" buttons functional—when clicked, show a confirmation modal: "Are you sure you want to rollback to version [X]?".
​3. Complete Ticket System:
​Chat Functionality: Allow the user to type a message and "Send" it. It should appear in the chat bubble list immediately.
​Visual Distinction: Ensure the "Internal Note" toggle works perfectly—turning the entire input area Yellow and changing the button text to "Post Staff Note."
​Status Management: Add a dropdown in the Ticket View to change the status (Open, Pending, Resolved). Changing it should update the badge color instantly.
​4. Security & Profile Completion:
​2FA Experience: In the Two-Factor tab, implement the "Setup" flow. Clicking "Enable" should show a mock QR code and a 6-digit input field.
​SSH Keys: Ensure the "Add Key" form works. Saved keys should be stored in localStorage so they stay there if the page is refreshed.
​5. Global "SaaS" Polish:
​Orange Link Audit: Double-check that every single instance of a Company name, Website name, or Environment ID is clickable and colored in Corefinity Orange.
​Breadcrumbs: Make the breadcrumbs dynamic so they reflect the user's current "navigation path" (e.g., Agency > Client > Production).
​Zero States: If a tab is empty, don't leave it blank; add a "Nothing here yet" illustration and a Call-to-Action button.
